# Project Testing

## Overview

Project Testing is the process of verifying that every component of OptiCrop functions as expected. The objective of testing was to identify defects, validate system behavior, and ensure that the application provides accurate crop recommendations under different input conditions.

Each module was tested independently before performing complete system integration.

---

# Testing Objectives

The testing phase was carried out to:

- Verify the correctness of every module.
- Ensure accurate crop prediction results.
- Validate user input before processing.
- Check communication between the frontend, backend, and database.
- Improve system reliability and stability.

---

# Testing Strategy

The application was tested in multiple stages to ensure complete functionality.

### Unit Testing

Each individual module was tested separately.

Modules tested:

- User Authentication
- Crop Prediction
- Database Operations
- Feedback Module

---

### Integration Testing

Integration testing verified communication between different components.

The following integrations were tested:

- Frontend ↔ Backend
- Backend ↔ Machine Learning Model
- Backend ↔ MongoDB Database

---

### Functional Testing

Functional testing confirmed that all project features behaved according to the requirements.

Features tested include:

- User Registration
- User Login
- Crop Recommendation
- Prediction History
- Feedback Submission

---

### System Testing

The complete application was tested as a single integrated system to verify end-to-end functionality.

The workflow tested was:

User Login → Enter Soil Parameters → Generate Prediction → Store Prediction → Display Result

---

